OL,3,CMental health trust fined #200,000 for
OL,4,Cdeaths under its care
OL,6,FThe Tees, Esk and Wear Valley NHS
OL,7,FFoundation Trust pleaded guilty in
OL,8,FSeptember last year to 'failing to
OL,9,Fprovide safe care and treatment to two
OL,10,Fpeople who were exposed to a
OL,11,Fsignificant risk of avoidable harm'.
OL,13,FChristie Harnett, 17, from Newton
OL,14,FAycliffe, County Durham, and an
OL,15,Funnamed woman, referred to as Patient
OL,16,FX, took their own lives using taps in
OL,17,Ftheir rooms that had already been
OL,18,Fflagged by the NHS as a risk but were
OL,19,Fnot removed.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/15
