OL,6,F"Everywhere we go we have memories
OL,7,Fwith Christie and it hurts like hell.
OL,8,FWe always visit places she loves and
OL,9,Fpick out clothes she would have worn.
OL,10,FEvery happy moment in my life is
OL,11,Ftinged with sadness.
OL,13,F"She is spoken about everyday and
OL,14,Falways will be. Her death was a
OL,15,Fmassive trauma. I can't remember her
OL,16,Fdying. I can't remember her funeral.
OL,17,FIt's a fuzzy blur. I have spent almost
OL,18,Ffive years holding it together.
OL,20,F"If anyone asks I just say I am ok but
OL,21,FI am not."
