OL,6,F"My granddaughter died a death that in
OL,7,Fmy opinion was wholly avoidable and
OL,8,Fwhich has broken our family. "
OL,10,FThe mother of Patient X also read an
OL,11,Femotional tribute in court, saying:
OL,12,F"The death of my daughter isn't like
OL,13,Fanything you can comprehend. I
OL,14,Fwouldn't wish the pain and anger on my
OL,15,Fworst enemy.
OL,17,F"I know I have to be strong for her
OL,18,Fchildren but I haven't had the
OL,19,Fopportunity to grieve. The only
OL,20,Fglimmer of hope is that she lives on
OL,21,Fin them.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/15
