OL,6,F"The trust failed to learn from
OL,7,Fearlier incidents, which could
OL,8,Fpotentially have avoided these tragic
OL,9,Foutcomes. The trust should have
OL,10,Fensured they were providing safe care
OL,11,Fand treatment to minimise the risks to
OL,12,FChristie and person X, however, sadly
OL,13,Fthis was not the case.
OL,15,F"I hope this prosecution reminds
OL,16,Fhealth and social care organisations
OL,17,Fthey must provide care in a safe way
OL,18,Fthat meets the needs of people, so
OL,19,Fthey receive the safe care and
OL,20,Ftreatment they deserve."
